---
/**
 * advanced-ai-systems/0001 · Figure 1 — the HERO ("one agent vs a fleet").
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/advanced-ai-systems/lessons/0001-multi-agent-systems-
 * when-and-when-not.html (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>).
 * Uses the shared arrowhead markers (#arw, #arwG, #arwR) defined by <Fig0>, which
 * the MDX renders once before this figure. Kept as an .astro component, NOT inline
 * in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG using
 * kebab-case attrs (text-anchor, font-size, marker-end, stroke-dasharray, …) and
 * self-referential ids. SVG anchor ids (r1, r1b) match the source DOM + #s1 footnote.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 300"
        role="img"
        aria-label="One agent versus a fleet: a fleet only wins when the work is genuinely parallel and the coordination tax is paid back; otherwise the single agent dominates."
    >
        <!-- the decision spine -->
        <rect
            x="40"
            y="130"
            width="120"
            height="44"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="100" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >A goal</text
        >
        <text x="100" y="165" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">one task to do</text
        >
        <rect
            x="260"
            y="130"
            width="120"
            height="44"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Is it parallel?</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="165" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >independent sub-work</text
        >
        <rect
            x="480"
            y="130"
            width="120"
            height="44"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="540" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Answer</text
        >
        <text x="540" y="165" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >cheap + debuggable</text
        >
        <line x1="160" y1="152" x2="256" y2="152" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="380" y1="152" x2="476" y2="152" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- the default badge -->
        <rect
            x="40"
            y="34"
            width="240"
            height="62"
            rx="10"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="160" y="54" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Default · ONE well-tooled agent</text
        >
        <text x="160" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >all state in one context</text
        >
        <text x="160" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >cheaper, lower-latency, one place to debug</text
        >

        <!-- the fleet badge -->
        <rect
            x="360"
            y="34"
            width="240"
            height="62"
            rx="10"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="480" y="54" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Only if parallel · a FLEET of agents</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >throughput on independent work</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >pays a coordination tax in tokens + latency</text
        >

        <line
            x1="160"
            y1="96"
            x2="120"
            y2="128"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <line
            x1="480"
            y1="96"
            x2="540"
            y2="128"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <text x="320" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">no &rarr;</text>
        <text x="430" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">&larr; yes</text>

        <text x="320" y="216" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e"
            >More agents add parallel hands, not a smarter brain.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="240" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >A multi-agent system is the distributed-systems version of an agent — same trade as a
            monolith vs microservices.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="276" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Don't add agents for the reasons you wouldn't add microservices.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The whole lesson in one picture. The single well-tooled agent is the <em>default</em>; a
        fleet is a scaling pattern you reach for only when work is genuinely parallel and the <b
            >coordination tax</b
        > pays for itself.<sup><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
